Package model

Class MyEngine

java.lang.Object
framework.Engine
model.MyEngine
public class MyEngine extends Engine
The MyEngine class extends the Engine class and simulates a gas station with multiple service points. It handles the arrival of customers, their routing through various service points, and the collection of simulation results.

    • MyEngine

      public MyEngine(Double refuelM, Double refuelV, Double washM, Double washV, Double shopM, Double shopV, Double payM, Double payV, Double dryM, Double dryV, Double arrM, Double arrV, Double delay)
      Constructs a MyEngine instance with specified parameters for service points and arrival process.
      Parameters:
      refuelM - mean service time for refuelling
      refuelV - variance of service time for refuelling
      washM - mean service time for washing
      washV - variance of service time for washing
      shopM - mean service time for shopping
      shopV - variance of service time for shopping
      payM - mean service time for paying
      payV - variance of service time for paying
      dryM - mean service time for drying
      dryV - variance of service time for drying
      arrM - mean arrival time
      arrV - variance of arrival time
